   316	### §0.6 Visibility
   317	
   318	`OpenReport` (`fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:548-554`) gains two booleans
   319	that together describe the workspace's mean-centering state. They are
   320	deliberately split into a **static identity capability** and a **dynamic
   321	workspace state** so that callers do not have to derive one from the
   322	other:
   323	
   324	```rust
   325	pub struct OpenReport {
   326	    // ... existing fields ...
   327	
   328	    /// Static: does this embedder identity REQUIRE mean-centering as
   329	    /// part of its sign-quantization pipeline? True iff the identity
   330	    /// recorded in `_fathomdb_embedder_profiles.identity_name` is one
   331	    /// whose pinned protocol uses MC (true for the 0.7.1 default
   332	    /// `fathomdb-bge-small-en-v1.5`; false for `fathomdb-noop` and any
   333	    /// caller-supplied embedder that does not opt in).
   334	    ///
   335	    /// This bool does NOT change over the workspace's lifetime — it is
   336	    /// determined by the embedder identity, which is itself fail-closed
   337	    /// after first profile-pin per ADR-0.6.0-vector-identity-embedder-owned.
   338	    pub embedder_mean_centering_required: bool,
   339	
   340	    /// Dynamic: has this workspace materialized the pinned mean vector
   341	    /// yet? True iff `_fathomdb_embedder_profiles.mean_vec IS NOT NULL`.
   342	    /// When `embedder_mean_centering_required == true` AND this is
   343	    /// `false`, the workspace is in the pre-pin window (count < 256);
   344	    /// when both are `true`, the workspace is in steady state. When
   345	    /// `required == false`, this field is always `false` (no mean is
   346	    /// ever pinned for an identity that does not use MC) — callers
   347	    /// inspecting just this bool MUST also read `required` to interpret
   348	    /// it.
   349	    pub embedder_mean_vec_pinned: bool,
   350	}
   351	```
   352	
   353	**Truth-table for the two bools:**
   354	
   355	| `required` | `pinned` | meaning                                                                |
   356	|------------|----------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|
   357	| false      | false    | Embedder identity does not use MC (e.g. `fathomdb-noop`, custom impl). |
   358	| false      | true     | **Impossible by construction.** Engine asserts in debug; release falls back to treating as `(false, false)`. |
   359	| true       | false    | MC-required identity, workspace in pre-pin window (count < 256).        |
   360	| true       | true     | MC-required identity, steady state. Sign-quant bits centered everywhere.|
   361	
   362	The `(false, true)` cell is impossible because pinning `mean_vec` is
   363	only performed by the projection worker after observing an MC-required
   364	identity. EU-5 includes a regression test that asserts this combination
   365	cannot occur via any public API.
   366	
   367	A `MeanVecPinned { dim, doc_count }` event is appended to
   368	`embedder_events` (see §7) on the commit that materializes the pinned
   369	mean (and atomically performs the §0.5 re-quantize pass). This is the
   370	only structured visibility into the pin transition.
   371	
   372	### §0.7 Invariant summary
   373	
   374	- Pinned `mean_vec` length in bytes equals `4 × embedder_identity.dimension`.
   375	- f32 BLOBs stored in the index are un-centered.
   376	- The f32 rerank distance is cosine over un-centered, L2-normed vectors.
   377	- Centering is applied if and only if
   378	  (`embedder_mean_centering_required == true` AND `mean_vec IS NOT NULL`);
   379	  else the sign-quantize path runs on un-centered vectors.
   380	- After the pin commit's atomic re-quantize pass (§0.5), every row in
   381	  the workspace's vector tables has sign-quant bits computed under the
   382	  same pinned mean — no row uses a different centering than any other.
