     1	//! Default-embedder weight loader.
     2	//!
     3	//! Implements the contract specified in
     4	//! `dev/plans/prompts/0.7.1-EMBEDDER-UNDEFER-HANDOFF.md` §EU-3 (which
     5	//! itself materialises `dev/design/embedder.md` §§1–10):
     6	//!
     7	//! 1. HF resolve URL pattern, three pinned files, sha256 pinned in Rust.
     8	//! 2. `ureq` blocking transport, 10s connect / 60s read, 3-attempt backoff,
     9	//!    Range resume on partial.
    10	//! 3. `HF_TOKEN` env var → `Authorization: Bearer`. No keychain. No file.
    11	//! 4. `<dirs::cache_dir>/fathomdb/embedders/<model-sha-prefix>/<file>`;
    12	//!    best-effort read-only probe of `~/.cache/huggingface` for users who
    13	//!    already have the file.
    14	//! 5. `.partial` → fsync → rename.
    15	//! 6. sha256-verify; on mismatch remove `.partial` and fail with
    16	//!    `EmbedderLoadError::ChecksumMismatch`. No trust-on-first-use.
    17	//! 7. Returns `Vec<EmbedderEvent>` so EU-5 can splice it into
    18	//!    `OpenReport.embedder_events` without re-running the work.
    19	//! 9. `EmbedderLoadError` taxonomy mirrors the design.
    20	//! 10. `fs2::FileExt::lock_exclusive` on a `.lock` sibling for the cache
    21	//!     directory; held only during fetch+verify+rename; cache-hit path does
    22	//!     NOT take the lock.
    23	//!
    24	//! Candle / `BertModel` construction is **EU-4** and is intentionally NOT
    25	//! in this slice. The loader's deliverable is byte-buffer-backed file
    26	//! paths plus an events log.
    27	//!
    28	//! ## Scope guardrails (ADR-0.7.1-default-embedder-weight-fetch)
    29	//!
    30	//! Pinned constants are `pub(crate) const`, not `pub const`. No public
    31	//! function takes a `&str` model name, URL, or repo. The only way to
    32	//! reach the loader from outside this module is the zero-arg entry
    33	//! point `load_pinned_default_embedder()`. Tests reach the override
    34	//! surface via `LoaderConfig::for_tests()` which is `cfg(any(test, ...))`
    35	//! gated — see the impl below.
    36	
